'''Rachel Clare Reuel Tolkien''' (born [[13 February]] [[1971]]) is the daughter of [[Baillie Tolkien]] and [[Christopher Tolkien]], sibling to [[Adam Tolkien]]. This makes [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] her grandfather.

Rachel Tolkien attended the world premiere of ''[[The Lord of the Rings (musical)]]'' in Toronto in 2006. She said that the "set is incredible, the costumes are beautiful," and that "[e]verything to me that is the most important, and the most moving in the book, they've gotten on the stage".<ref>{{webcite|author=|articleurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20060507145926/http://www.contracostatimes.com/mld/cctimes/news/14191031.htm|articlename=Tolkien's kin says 'Rings' play OK (archived)|dated=26 March 2006|website=[http://web.archive.org/web/20060507145926/http://www.contracostatimes.com/ ContraCostaTimes.com at WayBackMachine]|accessed=1 July 2013}}</ref>
Her last public appearance coincided with the French Tolkien exhibition in Paris, [https://www.lamontagne.fr/aubusson-23200/loisirs/lambassade-de-grande-bretagne-avant-la-bnf_13653111/ visiting the Embassy of the United Kingdom] with her mother Baillie where one of the Aubusson tapestries was exhibited.

